Description: For sale is a 1997 Paul Reed Smith Standard 24. Purchased in November 2016 for a project thatnever happened. Serial number 732915. Set neck, made in USA, moon inlays, all original with OHSC. Not an S2 or SE. Very clean, all original and very minor fret-wear. The guitar’s ended Reverb.com listing hasreally good pictures. The PRS model history page says basic set neck features by1985 were: Back angled 3 on-a-side non-veneered headstock One-piece mahogany glued in neck, regular shape 25” scale length, 24-fret Single-action truss rod (double action truss rod fitted fromlate ’91). 10” radiused Indian rosewood fretboard. Mother-of-pearl/Abalone moon inlays. One-piece mahogany body or back. Pickups changed to HFS Treble and Vintage Bass by November'91. PRS Tremolo System, Schaller/PRS locking tuners, lowfriction nut. PRS: 1985 – 1987 evolved from pre-’85 all-mahogany guitar,became the Standard in 1987. Small ding on the headstock near the 6-string tuner. Comeswith tremolo bar and OHSC. Weighs only 8lbs. Case has a few small tears in Tolexotherwise very good condition. Ships to a verifiable address CONUS only. Please ask questions before bidding.
